verbose_text: In the Terai, from 2007-2009, when our cohort was in pre-primary school, the overall Gross Enrolment Ratio (GER, total number of students enrolled in pre-primary, irrespective of age, expressed as a percentage of the official school-age population corresponding to the same level of education) was 64%, with 55% of children entering primary grade 1 having ECED experience in 2007.
